    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@nathanielmanistaatgoogle @kpayson64 I'm not sure we want this... Do we want this?\n\nI can see arguments in both directions:\n- For adding: `requirements.txt` isn't used except from the repository source, and we don't expect normal users to ever touch the repository source (even if they build from source, they're building from the source we've packaged up and dumped on PyPI).\n- Against: neither `pyyaml` nor `virtualenv` are requirements of the `grpcio` distribution, which the `requirements.txt` is supposed to be for.\n"
